    <refpurpose>The Lampadas Documentation System,
      for writing, managing and publishing documentation.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <simpara>The Lampadas Documentation System is a project of the
      Linux Documentation Project, one of the first and still one
      of the largest of all Linux projects.</simpara>

    <simpara>Lampadas is written by David Merrill &dhemail; and
      others. See the file <filename>CREDITS</filename>.</simpara>

    <simpara>This manual page is not intended to fully document
      Lampadas; that would be far outside the scope of a manual page.
      However, it does list the documentation that is available.</simpara>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>SEE ALSO</title>

    <simpara>The scripts that come with Lampadas all have their own manual
      pages. They include:</simpara>

    <variablelist>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>lampadasdb</term>
	<listitem><simpara
	  >A low-level utility to manage the data in your
	  database.</simpara
        ></listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>lampadasql</term>
	<listitem><simpara
	  >A low-level utility to update single tables of your
	  database.</simpara
        ></listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>

  </refsect1>
